{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":480,"text":"So I would like to start by telling you\nabout one of my greatest friends,"},{"time":5200,"text":"Okoloma Maduewesi."},{"time":7720,"text":"Okoloma lived on my street"},{"time":9360,"text":"and looked after me like a big brother."},{"time":11680,"text":"If I liked a boy,\nI would ask Okoloma's opinion."},{"time":16160,"text":"Okoloma died in the notorious\nSosoliso plane crash"},{"time":20040,"text":"in Nigeria in December of 2005."},{"time":23000,"text":"Almost exactly seven years ago."},{"time":26080,"text":"Okoloma was a person I could argue with,\nlaugh with and truly talk to."},{"time":31680,"text":"He was also the first person\nto call me a feminist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35520,"text":"I was about fourteen,\nwe were at his house, arguing."},{"time":38960,"text":"Both of us bristling\nwith half bit knowledge"},{"time":41480,"text":"from books that we had read."},{"time":43560,"text":"I don't remember what this\nparticular argument was about,"},{"time":47320,"text":"but I remember\nthat as I argued and argued,"},{"time":49400,"text":"Okoloma looked at me and said,\n\"You know, you're a feminist.\""},{"time":53880,"text":"It was not a compliment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":56560,"text":"I could tell from his tone,"},{"time":57920,"text":"the same tone that you would use\nto say something like,"},{"time":60720,"text":"\"You're a supporter of terrorism.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":62480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":65280,"text":"I did not know exactly\nwhat this word \"feminist\" meant,"},{"time":68960,"text":"and I did not want Okoloma\nto know that I did not know."},{"time":72200,"text":"So I brushed it aside,\nand I continued to argue."},{"time":75240,"text":"And the first thing\nI planned to do when I got home"},{"time":77680,"text":"was to look up the word\n\"feminist\" in the dictionary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80280,"text":"Now fast forward to some years later,"},{"time":83440,"text":"I wrote a novel about a man\nwho among other things beats his wife"},{"time":87600,"text":"and whose story doesn't end very well."},{"time":90600,"text":"While I was promoting\nthe novel in Nigeria,"},{"time":92680,"text":"a journalist, a nice, well-meaning man,"},{"time":95720,"text":"told me he wanted to advise me."},{"time":99280,"text":"And for the Nigerians here,"},{"time":100640,"text":"I'm sure we're all familiar"},{"time":102160,"text":"with how quick our people are\nto give unsolicited advice."},{"time":109760,"text":"He told me that people were saying\nthat my novel was feminist"},{"time":113240,"text":"and his advice to me --"},{"time":114880,"text":"and he was shaking his head\nsadly as he spoke --"},{"time":118080,"text":"was that I should never\ncall myself a feminist"},{"time":120280,"text":"because feminists\nare women who are unhappy"},{"time":122880,"text":"because they cannot find husbands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":129280,"text":"So I decided to call myself\n\"a happy feminist.\""},{"time":133040,"text":"Then an academic, a Nigerian woman told me"},{"time":135720,"text":"that feminism was not our culture"},{"time":137440,"text":"and that feminism wasn't African,"},{"time":139080,"text":"and that I was calling myself a feminist"},{"time":141040,"text":"because I had been corrupted\nby \"Western books.\""},{"time":144120,"text":"Which amused me,"},{"time":145360,"text":"because a lot of my early readings\nwere decidedly unfeminist."},{"time":148720,"text":"I think I must have read every single\nMills &amp; Boon romance published"},{"time":151960,"text":"before I was sixteen."},{"time":153960,"text":"And each time I tried to read those books"},{"time":155960,"text":"called \"the feminist classics,\""},{"time":157800,"text":"I'd get bored, and I really\nstruggled to finish them."},{"time":160600,"text":"But anyway, since feminism was un-African,"},{"time":163360,"text":"I decided that I would now call myself\n\"a happy African feminist.\""},{"time":167840,"text":"At some point I was a happy African\nfeminist who does not hate men"},{"time":172280,"text":"and who likes lip gloss"},{"time":173640,"text":"and who wears high heels\nfor herself but not for men."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":177920,"text":"Of course a lot of this\nwas tongue-in-cheek,"},{"time":180120,"text":"but that word feminist is so heavy\nwith baggage, negative baggage."},{"time":184760,"text":"You hate men, you hate bras,"},{"time":187120,"text":"you hate African culture,\nthat sort of thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190240,"text":"Now here's a story from my childhood."},{"time":193000,"text":"When I was in primary school,"},{"time":194800,"text":"my teacher said at the beginning of term\nthat she would give the class a test"},{"time":199360,"text":"and whoever got the highest score\nwould be the class monitor."},{"time":202320,"text":"Now, class monitor was a big deal."},{"time":205240,"text":"If you were a class monitor,"},{"time":207000,"text":"you got to write down\nthe names of noisemakers --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":209480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":211160,"text":"which was having enough power of its own."},{"time":214480,"text":"But my teacher would also give you\na cane to hold in your hand"},{"time":219280,"text":"while you walk around\nand patrol the class for noisemakers."},{"time":223360,"text":"Now, of course you were not\nactually allowed to use the cane."},{"time":226920,"text":"But it was an exciting prospect\nfor the nine-year-old me."},{"time":230360,"text":"I very much wanted\nto be the class monitor."},{"time":233160,"text":"And I got the highest score on the test."},{"time":235800,"text":"Then, to my surprise, my teacher said\nthat the monitor had to be a boy."},{"time":240240,"text":"She had forgotten\nto make that clear earlier"},{"time":242360,"text":"because she assumed it was ... obvious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244242,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":246320,"text":"A boy had the second highest\nscore on the test,"},{"time":249120,"text":"and he would be monitor."},{"time":251960,"text":"Now, what was even more\ninteresting about this"},{"time":254160,"text":"is that the boy was a sweet, gentle soul"},{"time":258000,"text":"who had no interest\nin patrolling the class with the cane,"},{"time":262120,"text":"while I was full of ambition to do so."},{"time":266560,"text":"But I was female and he was male,"},{"time":268680,"text":"and so he became the class monitor."},{"time":271240,"text":"And I've never forgotten that incident."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274160,"text":"I often make the mistake of thinking"},{"time":276080,"text":"that something that is obvious to me\nis just as obvious to everyone else."},{"time":279560,"text":"Now, take my dear friend Louis"},{"time":281160,"text":"for example."},{"time":282520,"text":"Louis is a brilliant, progressive man,"},{"time":284400,"text":"and we would have conversations\nand he would tell me,"},{"time":286920,"text":"\"I don't know what you mean by things\nbeing different or harder for women."},{"time":290960,"text":"Maybe in the past, but not now.\""},{"time":293560,"text":"And I didn't understand how Louis\ncould not see what seems so self-evident."},{"time":298160,"text":"Then one evening, in Lagos,\nLouis and I went out with friends."},{"time":302320,"text":"And for people here\nwho are not familiar with Lagos,"},{"time":304800,"text":"there's that wonderful Lagos' fixture,"},{"time":306720,"text":"the sprinkling of energetic men\nwho hang around outside establishments"},{"time":311400,"text":"and very dramatically\n\"help\" you park your car."},{"time":316000,"text":"I was impressed\nwith the particular theatrics"},{"time":319320,"text":"of the man who found us\na parking spot that evening."},{"time":322320,"text":"And so as we were leaving,\nI decided to leave him a tip."},{"time":326760,"text":"I opened my bag,"},{"time":328200,"text":"put my hand inside my bag,"},{"time":329600,"text":"brought out my money\nthat I had earned from doing my work,"},{"time":333160,"text":"and I gave it to the man."},{"time":335600,"text":"And he, this man who was\nvery grateful and very happy,"},{"time":340000,"text":"took the money from me,"},{"time":341800,"text":"looked across at Louis"},{"time":343240,"text":"and said, \"Thank you, sir!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":345120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":351160,"text":"Louis looked at me, surprised,"},{"time":354440,"text":"and asked, \"Why is he thanking me?\nI didn't give him the money.\""},{"time":358840,"text":"Then I saw realization\ndawn on Louis' face."},{"time":363040,"text":"The man believed that whatever money I had"},{"time":365480,"text":"had ultimately come from Louis."},{"time":369720,"text":"Because Louis is a man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372600,"text":"Men and women are different."},{"time":374440,"text":"We have different hormones,\nwe have different sexual organs,"},{"time":377320,"text":"we have different biological abilities."},{"time":379400,"text":"Women can have babies, men can't."},{"time":382800,"text":"At least not yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384040,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":385480,"text":"Men have testosterone and are\nin general physically stronger than women."},{"time":390520,"text":"There's slightly more women\nthan men in the world,"},{"time":393200,"text":"about 52 percent of the world's\npopulation is female."},{"time":396320,"text":"But most of the positions of power\nand prestige are occupied by men."},{"time":400840,"text":"The late Kenyan Nobel Peace laureate,"},{"time":403320,"text":"Wangari Maathai,"},{"time":404680,"text":"put it simply and well when she said:"},{"time":407600,"text":"\"The higher you go,\nthe fewer women there are.\""},{"time":411920,"text":"In the recent US elections we kept hearing\nof the Lilly Ledbetter law,"},{"time":416560,"text":"and if we go beyond the nicely\nalliterative name of that law,"},{"time":420000,"text":"it was really about a man and a woman"},{"time":422160,"text":"doing the same job,\nbeing equally qualified,"},{"time":424960,"text":"and the man being paid more\nbecause he's a man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428160,"text":"So in the literal way, men rule the world,"},{"time":431520,"text":"and this made sense a thousand years ago"},{"time":435120,"text":"because human beings lived then in a world"},{"time":438000,"text":"in which physical strength was\nthe most important attribute for survival."},{"time":442200,"text":"The physically stronger person\nwas more likely to lead,"},{"time":447280,"text":"and men, in general,\nare physically stronger."},{"time":449880,"text":"Of course there are many exceptions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451619,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":453200,"text":"But today we live\nin a vastly different world."},{"time":457720,"text":"The person more likely to lead\nis not the physically stronger person;"},{"time":461800,"text":"it is the more creative person,\nthe more intelligent person,"},{"time":465320,"text":"the more innovative person,"},{"time":467760,"text":"and there are no hormones\nfor those attributes."},{"time":470440,"text":"A man is as likely as a woman\nto be intelligent,"},{"time":473080,"text":"to be creative, to be innovative."},{"time":475800,"text":"We have evolved;"},{"time":477120,"text":"but it seems to me that our ideas\nof gender had not evolved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481760,"text":"Some weeks ago, I walked into a lobby\nof one of the best Nigerian hotels."},{"time":486280,"text":"I thought about naming the hotel,\nbut I thought I probably shouldn't."},{"time":489560,"text":"And a guard at the entrance stopped me\nand asked me annoying questions,"},{"time":493960,"text":"because their automatic assumption is"},{"time":495800,"text":"that a Nigerian female walking\ninto a hotel alone is a sex worker."},{"time":501000,"text":"And by the way,"},{"time":502240,"text":"why do these hotels\nfocus on the ostensible supply"},{"time":505400,"text":"rather than the demand for sex workers?"},{"time":509520,"text":"In Lagos I cannot go alone\ninto many \"reputable\" bars and clubs."},{"time":514799,"text":"They just don't let you in\nif you're a woman alone,"},{"time":517240,"text":"you have to be accompanied by a man."},{"time":519600,"text":"Each time I walk into\na Nigerian restaurant with a man,"},{"time":522360,"text":"the waiter greets the man and ignores me."},{"time":526320,"text":"The waiters are products --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":527840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":529000,"text":"At this some women\nfelt like, \"Yes! I thought that!\""},{"time":531920,"text":"The waiters are products of a society"},{"time":533880,"text":"that has taught them that men\nare more important than women."},{"time":538240,"text":"And I know that waiters\ndon't intend any harm."},{"time":541120,"text":"But it's one thing to know intellectually\nand quite another to feel it emotionally."},{"time":545440,"text":"Each time they ignore me,\nI feel invisible."},{"time":547840,"text":"I feel upset."},{"time":549720,"text":"I want to tell them\nthat I am just as human as the man,"},{"time":553080,"text":"that I'm just as worthy of acknowledgment."},{"time":556760,"text":"These are little things,"},{"time":558040,"text":"but sometimes it's the little things\nthat sting the most."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561320,"text":"And not long ago, I wrote an article"},{"time":563080,"text":"about what it means\nto be young and female in Lagos,"},{"time":566400,"text":"and the printers told me,"},{"time":569120,"text":"\"It was so angry.\""},{"time":570960,"text":"Of course it was angry!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":572360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":576840,"text":"I am angry."},{"time":578520,"text":"Gender as it functions today\nis a grave injustice."},{"time":581680,"text":"We should all be angry."},{"time":583440,"text":"Anger has a long history\nof bringing about positive change;"},{"time":587320,"text":"but, in addition to being angry,\nI'm also hopeful."},{"time":590880,"text":"Because I believe deeply\nin the ability of human beings"},{"time":593520,"text":"to make and remake\nthemselves for the better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596920,"text":"Gender matters everywhere in the world,"},{"time":598840,"text":"but I want to focus on Nigeria"},{"time":601520,"text":"and on Africa in general,"},{"time":603000,"text":"because it is where I know,\nand because it is where my heart is."},{"time":606600,"text":"And I would like today to ask"},{"time":608560,"text":"that we begin to dream about\nand plan for a different world,"},{"time":612720,"text":"a fairer world,"},{"time":616240,"text":"a world of happier men and happier women\nwho are truer to themselves."},{"time":620440,"text":"And this is how to start:"},{"time":622000,"text":"we must raise our daughters differently."},{"time":624480,"text":"We must also raise our sons differently."},{"time":628000,"text":"We do a great disservice to boys\non how we raise them;"},{"time":631680,"text":"we stifle the humanity of boys."},{"time":634480,"text":"We define masculinity\nin a very narrow way,"},{"time":637080,"text":"masculinity becomes this hard, small cage"},{"time":640600,"text":"and we put boys inside the cage."},{"time":642920,"text":"We teach boys to be afraid of fear."},{"time":645480,"text":"We teach boys to be afraid\nof weakness, of vulnerability."},{"time":650200,"text":"We teach them to mask their true selves,"},{"time":652680,"text":"because they have to be,\nin Nigerian speak, \"hard man!\""},{"time":658440,"text":"In secondary school, a boy and a girl,\nboth of them teenagers,"},{"time":662600,"text":"both of them with the same amount\nof pocket money, would go out"},{"time":666120,"text":"and then the boy\nwould be expected always to pay,"},{"time":668920,"text":"to prove his masculinity."},{"time":671440,"text":"And yet we wonder why boys are more likely\nto steal money from their parents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677240,"text":"What if both boys and girls were raised"},{"time":680760,"text":"not to link masculinity with money?"},{"time":683720,"text":"What if the attitude\nwas not \"the boy has to pay\""},{"time":686760,"text":"but rather \"whoever has more should pay?\""},{"time":690360,"text":"Now, of course because\nof that historical advantage,"},{"time":692960,"text":"it is mostly men who will have more today,"},{"time":695440,"text":"but if we start\nraising children differently,"},{"time":698080,"text":"then in fifty years, in a hundred years,"},{"time":700640,"text":"boys will no longer have the pressure\nof having to prove this masculinity."},{"time":705680,"text":"But by far the worst thing we do to males,"},{"time":708720,"text":"by making them feel\nthat they have to be hard,"},{"time":711080,"text":"is that we leave them\nwith very fragile egos."},{"time":715120,"text":"The more \"hard man\"\nthe man feels compelled to be,"},{"time":719320,"text":"the weaker his ego is."},{"time":722960,"text":"And then we do a much greater\ndisservice to girls"},{"time":726000,"text":"because we raise them\nto cater to the fragile egos of men."},{"time":730200,"text":"We teach girls to shrink themselves,\nto make themselves smaller,"},{"time":733720,"text":"we say to girls,"},{"time":735640,"text":"\"You can have ambition, but not too much.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":737840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":739240,"text":"\"You should aim to be successful,\nbut not too successful,"},{"time":741960,"text":"otherwise you would threaten the man.\""},{"time":744720,"text":"If you are the breadwinner\nin your relationship with a man,"},{"time":747640,"text":"you have to pretend that you're not,"},{"time":749640,"text":"especially in public,"},{"time":751320,"text":"otherwise you will emasculate him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754720,"text":"But what if we question\nthe premise itself?"},{"time":757080,"text":"Why should a woman's success\nbe a threat to a man?"},{"time":761200,"text":"What if we decide\nto simply dispose of that word,"},{"time":764760,"text":"and I don't think there's an English word\nI dislike more than \"emasculation.\""},{"time":770720,"text":"A Nigerian acquaintance once asked me"},{"time":773040,"text":"if I was worried that men\nwould be intimidated by me."},{"time":776560,"text":"I was not worried at all."},{"time":778320,"text":"In fact, it had not occurred\nto me to be worried"},{"time":780600,"text":"because a man who would\nbe intimidated by me"},{"time":782840,"text":"is exactly the kind of man\nI would have no interest in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":786720,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":794120,"text":"But still I was really struck by this."},{"time":797640,"text":"Because I'm female,\nI'm expected to aspire to marriage;"},{"time":801960,"text":"I'm expected to make my life choices"},{"time":803760,"text":"always keeping in mind\nthat marriage is the most important."},{"time":808040,"text":"A marriage can be a good thing;"},{"time":810040,"text":"it can be a source of joy\nand love and mutual support."},{"time":814480,"text":"But why do we teach girls\nto aspire to marriage"},{"time":816960,"text":"and we don't teach boys the same?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":820840,"text":"I know a woman\nwho decided to sell her house"},{"time":823040,"text":"because she didn't want\nto intimidate a man who might marry her."},{"time":827880,"text":"I know an unmarried woman in Nigeria\nwho, when she goes to conferences,"},{"time":832360,"text":"wears a wedding ring"},{"time":833760,"text":"because according to her,"},{"time":835000,"text":"she wants the other participants\nin the conference to \"give her respect.\""},{"time":840120,"text":"I know young women\nwho are under so much pressure"},{"time":842480,"text":"from family, from friends,\neven from work to get married,"},{"time":846600,"text":"and they're pushed\nto make terrible choices."},{"time":849520,"text":"A woman at a certain age who is unmarried,"},{"time":852160,"text":"our society teaches her\nto see it as a deep, personal failure."},{"time":857040,"text":"And a man at a certain age\nwho is unmarried,"},{"time":859840,"text":"we just think he hasn't come around\nto making his pick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":862480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":864360,"text":"It's easy for us to say,"},{"time":866000,"text":"\"Oh, but women can\njust say no to all of this.\""},{"time":868280,"text":"But the reality is more difficult\nand more complex."},{"time":871360,"text":"We're all social beings."},{"time":873160,"text":"We internalize ideas\nfrom our socialization."},{"time":875680,"text":"Even the language we use"},{"time":877680,"text":"in talking about marriage\nand relationships illustrates this."},{"time":881120,"text":"The language of marriage\nis often the language of ownership"},{"time":884000,"text":"rather than the language of partnership."},{"time":886800,"text":"We use the word \"respect\""},{"time":889520,"text":"to mean something a woman shows a man"},{"time":892320,"text":"but often not something\na man shows a woman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896160,"text":"Both men and women in Nigeria will say --"},{"time":898640,"text":"this is an expression\nI'm very amused by --"},{"time":900960,"text":"\"I did it for peace in my marriage.\""},{"time":904400,"text":"Now, when men say it,"},{"time":906000,"text":"it is usually about something\nthat they should not be doing anyway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":909200,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":911160,"text":"Sometimes they say it to their friends,"},{"time":913960,"text":"it's something to say to their friends\nin a kind of fondly exasperated way,"},{"time":917920,"text":"you know, something that ultimately\nproves how masculine they are,"},{"time":921080,"text":"how needed, how loved."},{"time":922560,"text":"\"Oh, my wife said\nI can't go to the club every night,"},{"time":925080,"text":"so for peace in my marriage,\nI do it only on weekends.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":927920,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":929640,"text":"Now, when a woman says,\n\"I did it for peace in my marriage,\""},{"time":933920,"text":"she's usually talking\nabout giving up a job,"},{"time":937480,"text":"a dream,"},{"time":938960,"text":"a career."},{"time":941080,"text":"We teach females that in relationships,"},{"time":943520,"text":"compromise is what women do."},{"time":947080,"text":"We raise girls to see\neach other as competitors --"},{"time":949680,"text":"not for jobs or for accomplishments,\nwhich I think can be a good thing,"},{"time":953160,"text":"but for attention of men."},{"time":955920,"text":"We teach girls that they\ncannot be sexual beings"},{"time":958880,"text":"in the way that boys are."},{"time":960400,"text":"If we have sons, we don't mind\nknowing about our sons' girlfriends."},{"time":964480,"text":"But our daughters' boyfriends? God forbid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":966840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":968480,"text":"But of course when the time is right,"},{"time":970320,"text":"we expect those girls to bring back\nthe perfect man to be their husbands."},{"time":974240,"text":"We police girls,\nwe praise girls for virginity,"},{"time":977640,"text":"but we don't praise boys for virginity,"},{"time":979600,"text":"and it's always made me wonder how exactly\nthis is supposed to work out because ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":983529,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":985880,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":993760,"text":"I mean, the loss of virginity\nis usually a process that involves ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":998680,"text":"Recently a young woman\nwas gang raped in a university in Nigeria,"},{"time":1002880,"text":"I think some of us know about that."},{"time":1004600,"text":"And the response of many young Nigerians,\nboth male and female,"},{"time":1007880,"text":"was something along the lines of this:"},{"time":1010400,"text":"\"Yes, rape is wrong."},{"time":1012600,"text":"But what is a girl doing\nin a room with four boys?\""},{"time":1016920,"text":"Now, if we can forget\nthe horrible inhumanity of that response,"},{"time":1022080,"text":"these Nigerians have been raised\nto think of women as inherently guilty,"},{"time":1027319,"text":"and they have been raised\nto expect so little of men"},{"time":1030480,"text":"that the idea of men as savage beings\nwithout any control"},{"time":1034200,"text":"is somehow acceptable."},{"time":1036839,"text":"We teach girls shame."},{"time":1038880,"text":"\"Close your legs.\" \"Cover yourself.\""},{"time":1041440,"text":"We make them feel\nas though by being born female"},{"time":1043720,"text":"they're already guilty of something."},{"time":1045839,"text":"And so, girls grow up to be women"},{"time":1048200,"text":"who cannot see they have desire."},{"time":1050360,"text":"They grow up to be women\nwho silence themselves."},{"time":1055080,"text":"They grow up to be women\nwho cannot say what they truly think,"},{"time":1058520,"text":"and they grow up --"},{"time":1059880,"text":"and this is the worst thing\nwe did to girls --"},{"time":1062080,"text":"they grow up to be women\nwho have turned pretense into an art form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1066240,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1072440,"text":"I know a woman who hates domestic work,"},{"time":1075880,"text":"she just hates it,"},{"time":1077400,"text":"but she pretends that she likes it,"},{"time":1080200,"text":"because she's been taught\nthat to be \"good wife material\""},{"time":1084320,"text":"she has to be --\nto use that Nigerian word --"},{"time":1086720,"text":"very \"homely.\""},{"time":1089440,"text":"And then she got married,"},{"time":1091000,"text":"and after a while her husband's family\nbegan to complain that she had changed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1094840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1096440,"text":"Actually, she had not changed,"},{"time":1097920,"text":"she just got tired of pretending."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1100720,"text":"The problem with gender,"},{"time":1103880,"text":"is that it prescribes how we should be"},{"time":1106440,"text":"rather than recognizing how we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1109400,"text":"Now imagine how much happier we would be,"},{"time":1111880,"text":"how much freer to be\nour true individual selves,"},{"time":1115400,"text":"if we didn't have the weight\nof gender expectations."},{"time":1119240,"text":"Boys and girls are\nundeniably different biologically,"},{"time":1124040,"text":"but socialization\nexaggerates the differences"},{"time":1127040,"text":"and then it becomes\na self-fulfilling process."},{"time":1129640,"text":"Now, take cooking for example."},{"time":1132280,"text":"Today women in general are more likely\nto do the housework than men,"},{"time":1135800,"text":"the cooking and cleaning."},{"time":1137080,"text":"But why is that?"},{"time":1138680,"text":"Is it because women\nare born with a cooking gene?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1141560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1143000,"text":"Or because over years they have been\nsocialized to see cooking as their role?"},{"time":1147280,"text":"Actually, I was going to say that maybe\nwomen are born with a cooking gene,"},{"time":1150880,"text":"until I remember that the majority\nof the famous cooks in the world,"},{"time":1154360,"text":"whom we give the fancy title of \"chefs,\""},{"time":1156680,"text":"are men."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1158960,"text":"I used to look up to my grandmother"},{"time":1160680,"text":"who was a brilliant, brilliant woman,"},{"time":1162760,"text":"and wonder how she would have been"},{"time":1164520,"text":"if she had the same opportunities\nas men when she was growing up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1168960,"text":"Now today, there are\nmany more opportunities for women"},{"time":1171560,"text":"than there were\nduring my grandmother's time"},{"time":1173840,"text":"because of changes in policy,\nchanges in law,"},{"time":1176480,"text":"all of which are very important."},{"time":1178080,"text":"But what matters even more\nis our attitude, our mindset,"},{"time":1182640,"text":"what we believe\nand what we value about gender."},{"time":1185960,"text":"What if in raising children"},{"time":1188400,"text":"we focus on ability instead of gender?"},{"time":1192000,"text":"What if in raising children\nwe focus on interest instead of gender?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1197000,"text":"I know a family\nwho have a son and a daughter,"},{"time":1199240,"text":"both of whom are brilliant at school,"},{"time":1201160,"text":"who are wonderful, lovely children."},{"time":1203080,"text":"When the boy is hungry,\nthe parents say to the girl,"},{"time":1205640,"text":"\"Go and cook Indomie noodles\nfor your brother.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1207880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1209120,"text":"Now, the daughter doesn't\nparticularly like to cook Indomie noodles,"},{"time":1212640,"text":"but she's a girl, and so she has to."},{"time":1215440,"text":"Now, what if the parents,"},{"time":1217240,"text":"from the beginning,"},{"time":1218880,"text":"taught both the boy and the girl\nto cook Indomie?"},{"time":1223920,"text":"Cooking, by the way,\nis a very useful skill for boys to have."},{"time":1226960,"text":"I've never thought it made sense\nto leave such a crucial thing,"},{"time":1231840,"text":"the ability to nourish oneself --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1233760,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1235000,"text":"in the hands of others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1236560,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1241760,"text":"I know a woman who has the same degree\nand the same job as her husband."},{"time":1245640,"text":"When they get back from work,\nshe does most of the housework,"},{"time":1248560,"text":"which I think is true for many marriages."},{"time":1250760,"text":"But what struck me about them"},{"time":1252520,"text":"was that whenever her husband\nchanged the baby's diaper,"},{"time":1255520,"text":"she said \"thank you\" to him."},{"time":1259040,"text":"Now, what if she saw this\nas perfectly normal and natural"},{"time":1263480,"text":"that he should, in fact,\ncare for his child?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1266840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1269680,"text":"I'm trying to unlearn\nmany of the lessons of gender"},{"time":1273200,"text":"that I internalized when I was growing up."},{"time":1275520,"text":"But I sometimes still feel very vulnerable\nin the face of gender expectations."},{"time":1280600,"text":"The first time I taught\na writing class in graduate school,"},{"time":1284360,"text":"I was worried."},{"time":1285640,"text":"I wasn't worried\nabout the material I would teach"},{"time":1288000,"text":"because I was well-prepared,"},{"time":1289360,"text":"and I was going to teach\nwhat I enjoy teaching."},{"time":1291600,"text":"Instead, I was worried about what to wear."},{"time":1294680,"text":"I wanted to be taken seriously."},{"time":1297480,"text":"I knew that because I was female"},{"time":1299080,"text":"I will automatically\nhave to prove my worth."},{"time":1303240,"text":"And I was worried\nthat if I looked too feminine,"},{"time":1305520,"text":"I would not be taken seriously."},{"time":1307320,"text":"I really wanted to wear\nmy shiny lip gloss and my girly skirt,"},{"time":1311680,"text":"but I decided not to."},{"time":1313520,"text":"Instead, I wore a very serious,"},{"time":1315920,"text":"very manly and very ugly suit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1318520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1320040,"text":"Because the sad truth is\nthat when it comes to appearance"},{"time":1322760,"text":"we start off with men\nas the standard, as the norm."},{"time":1325960,"text":"If a man is getting ready\nfor a business meeting,"},{"time":1328320,"text":"he doesn't worry\nabout looking too masculine"},{"time":1330480,"text":"and therefore not being taken for granted."},{"time":1333000,"text":"If a woman has to get ready\nfor business meeting,"},{"time":1335520,"text":"she has to worry\nabout looking too feminine"},{"time":1338320,"text":"and what it says and whether or not\nshe will be taken seriously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1344000,"text":"I wish I had not worn\nthat ugly suit that day."},{"time":1347440,"text":"I've actually banished it\nfrom my closet, by the way."},{"time":1350600,"text":"Had I then the confidence\nthat I have now to be myself,"},{"time":1355560,"text":"my students would have benefited\neven more from my teaching,"},{"time":1358520,"text":"because I would have been more comfortable"},{"time":1360600,"text":"and more fully and more truly myself."},{"time":1363800,"text":"I have chosen to no longer\nbe apologetic for my femaleness"},{"time":1367840,"text":"and for my femininity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1369680,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1375800,"text":"And I want to be respected\nin all of my femaleness"},{"time":1378680,"text":"because I deserve to be."},{"time":1381200,"text":"Gender is not an easy\nconversation to have."},{"time":1385080,"text":"For both men and women,"},{"time":1386680,"text":"to bring up gender is sometimes\nto encounter almost immediate resistance."},{"time":1390640,"text":"I can imagine some people here\nare actually thinking,"},{"time":1393920,"text":"\"Women too do sef.\""},{"time":1397520,"text":"Some of the men here might be thinking,"},{"time":1399720,"text":"\"OK, all of this is interesting,"},{"time":1401480,"text":"but I don't think like that.\""},{"time":1403960,"text":"And that is part of the problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1406200,"text":"That many men do not\nactively think about gender"},{"time":1409200,"text":"or notice gender"},{"time":1410720,"text":"is part of the problem of gender."},{"time":1412760,"text":"That many men, say, like my friend Louis,"},{"time":1415440,"text":"that everything is fine now."},{"time":1418160,"text":"And that many men do nothing to change it."},{"time":1421040,"text":"If you are a man and you walk\ninto a restaurant with a woman"},{"time":1423920,"text":"and the waiter greets only you,"},{"time":1426400,"text":"does it occur to you to ask the waiter,"},{"time":1428920,"text":"\"Why haven't you greeted her?\""},{"time":1433320,"text":"Because gender can be --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1434840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1444880,"text":"Actually, we may repose\npart of a longer version of this talk."},{"time":1449400,"text":"So, because gender can be\na very uncomfortable conversation to have,"},{"time":1453000,"text":"there are very easy ways to close it,\nto close the conversation."},{"time":1456120,"text":"So some people will bring up\nevolutionary biology and apes,"},{"time":1460320,"text":"how, you know, female apes\nbow down to male apes"},{"time":1464000,"text":"and that sort of thing."},{"time":1465880,"text":"But the point is we're not apes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1467960,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1469400,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1474160,"text":"Apes also live on trees\nand have earthworms for breakfast,"},{"time":1479000,"text":"and we don't."},{"time":1481240,"text":"Some people will say,\n\"Well, poor men also have a hard time.\""},{"time":1485880,"text":"And this is true."},{"time":1487920,"text":"But that is not what this --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1489280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1490400,"text":"But this is not\nwhat this conversation is about."},{"time":1494480,"text":"Gender and class\nare different forms of oppression."},{"time":1498280,"text":"I actually learned quite a bit\nabout systems of oppression"},{"time":1501960,"text":"and how they can be blind to one another"},{"time":1504440,"text":"by talking to black men."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1507320,"text":"I was once talking\nto a black man about gender"},{"time":1510520,"text":"and he said to me,"},{"time":1511920,"text":"\"Why do you have to say\n'my experience as a woman'?"},{"time":1515400,"text":"Why can't it be"},{"time":1516640,"text":"'your experience as a human being'?\""},{"time":1519840,"text":"Now, this was the same man"},{"time":1521120,"text":"who would often talk\nabout his experience as a black man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1527360,"text":"Gender matters."},{"time":1528600,"text":"Men and women\nexperience the world differently."},{"time":1531120,"text":"Gender colors the way\nwe experience the world."},{"time":1533960,"text":"But we can change that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1536520,"text":"Some people will say,"},{"time":1538480,"text":"\"Oh, but women have the real power,"},{"time":1540960,"text":"bottom power.\""},{"time":1542760,"text":"And for non-Nigerians,\nbottom power is an expression"},{"time":1545680,"text":"which I suppose means\nsomething like a woman"},{"time":1547560,"text":"who uses her sexuality\nto get favors from men."},{"time":1551200,"text":"But bottom power is not power at all."},{"time":1556400,"text":"Bottom power means that a woman"},{"time":1559200,"text":"simply has a good root to tap into,\nfrom time to time --"},{"time":1562120,"text":"somebody else's power."},{"time":1564640,"text":"And then, of course, we have to wonder"},{"time":1566520,"text":"what happens when\nthat somebody else is in a bad mood,"},{"time":1569200,"text":"or sick"},{"time":1570600,"text":"or impotent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1572280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1575720,"text":"Some people will say that a woman\nbeing subordinate to a man is our culture."},{"time":1582640,"text":"But culture is constantly changing."},{"time":1584640,"text":"I have beautiful twin nieces\nwho are fifteen and live in Lagos."},{"time":1589320,"text":"If they had been born a hundred years ago"},{"time":1592000,"text":"they would have been\ntaken away and killed."},{"time":1594160,"text":"Because it was our culture,\nit was our culture to kill twins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1599040,"text":"So what is the point of culture?"},{"time":1601480,"text":"I mean there's the decorative,"},{"time":1603080,"text":"the dancing ..."},{"time":1604720,"text":"but also, culture really is about\npreservation and continuity of a people."},{"time":1609360,"text":"In my family,"},{"time":1610640,"text":"I am the child who is most interested\nin the story of who we are,"},{"time":1613840,"text":"in our traditions,"},{"time":1615120,"text":"in the knowledge about ancestral lands."},{"time":1617320,"text":"My brothers are not as interested as I am."},{"time":1619920,"text":"But I cannot participate,"},{"time":1622200,"text":"I cannot go to umunna meetings,"},{"time":1624240,"text":"I cannot have a say."},{"time":1626000,"text":"Because I'm female."},{"time":1628080,"text":"Culture does not make people,"},{"time":1630200,"text":"people make culture."},{"time":1632920,"text":"So if it is in fact true --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1634720,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1638240,"text":"So if it is in fact true"},{"time":1639880,"text":"that the full humanity of women\nis not our culture,"},{"time":1642800,"text":"then we must make it our culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1646040,"text":"I think very often of my dear friend,\nOkoloma Maduewesi."},{"time":1651680,"text":"May he and all the others\nwho passed away in that Sosoliso crash"},{"time":1655680,"text":"continue to rest in peace."},{"time":1658400,"text":"He will always be remembered\nby those of us who loved him."},{"time":1662880,"text":"And he was right that day many years ago\nwhen he called me a feminist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1667400,"text":"I am a feminist."},{"time":1669400,"text":"And when I looked up the word\nin the dictionary that day,"},{"time":1672120,"text":"this is what it said:"},{"time":1673400,"text":"\"Feminist: a person\nwho believes in the social, political"},{"time":1676800,"text":"and economic equality of the sexes.\""},{"time":1680520,"text":"My great grandmother,\nfrom the stories I've heard,"},{"time":1683480,"text":"was a feminist."},{"time":1685080,"text":"She ran away from the house of the man\nshe did not want to marry"},{"time":1688480,"text":"and ended up marrying\nthe man of her choice."},{"time":1691160,"text":"She refused, she protested, she spoke up"},{"time":1694160,"text":"whenever she felt she was being deprived\nof access, of land, that sort of thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1699480,"text":"My great grandmother\ndid not know that word \"feminist,\""},{"time":1702800,"text":"but it doesn't mean that she wasn't one."},{"time":1706160,"text":"More of us should reclaim that word."},{"time":1710040,"text":"My own definition of feminist is:"},{"time":1713200,"text":"\"A feminist is a man or a woman"},{"time":1715600,"text":"who says --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1717480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1720640,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1726600,"text":"A feminist is a man or a woman who says,"},{"time":1729880,"text":"\"Yes, there's a problem\nwith gender as it is today,"},{"time":1733200,"text":"and we must fix it."},{"time":1734520,"text":"We must do better.\""},{"time":1737960,"text":"The best feminist I know"},{"time":1740040,"text":"is my brother Kene."},{"time":1742920,"text":"He's also a kind,\ngood-looking, lovely man,"},{"time":1746840,"text":"and he's very masculine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1749320,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1750560,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}